	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001011_0001"/><!--pb/@n='22r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>57 Sloane St</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">29<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">th</hi></hi> April</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1857 </p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">r</hi></hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I hear the 
<lb/>drawings are to 
<lb/>be taken down 
<lb/>at <placeName>Stafford 
<lb/>House</placeName> today. If you think 
<lb/>anything else 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001011_0002"/><!--pb/@n='22v'--> 
<lb/>is needed <persName>M<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">r</hi></hi> Wolf</persName>
<lb/>ought to go before 
<lb/>they are removed<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p>My brother will 
<lb/>be in <placeName>London</placeName>
<lb/>tomorrow evening<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>He will I daresay 
<lb/>help me on a 
<lb/>little quicker I 
<lb/>believe he left 
<lb/>before my advice 
<lb/>about Â£30 came 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001011_0003"/><!--pb/@n='23r'--> 
<lb/>to hand. <choice><reg>B</reg><orig>b</orig></choice>ut it is 
<lb/>safe. <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Binney</persName>
<lb/>has made a good 
<lb/>many corrections 
<lb/>I shall embody 
<lb/>yours &amp; his 
<lb/>together. He advised 
<lb/>a few sentences 
<lb/>on the change in 
<lb/>the feelings in my 
<lb/>history without 
<lb/>which many religious 
<lb/>people would set 
<lb/>the book down 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001011_0004"/><!--pb/@n='23v'--> 
<lb/>as a merely intellectual 
<lb/>affair and that 
<lb/>I was not a religious 
<lb/>missionary at all. 
<lb/>I do so in 4 or 5 
<lb/>sentences &amp; then 
<lb/>state that I will not 
<lb/>refer to the religious 
<lb/>feelings again not 
<lb/>to the evangelistic 
<lb/>labours to which 
<lb/>these impelled me 
<lb/>this will take away 
<lb/>the handle which 
<lb/>some might use 

	<pb n="0005" facs="liv_001011_0005"/><!--pb/@n='24r'--> 
<lb/>against it. <persName>M<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">r</hi></hi> Binney</persName>
<lb/>is pleased with it 
<lb/>and has also smoothed 
<lb/>some harsh sentences 
<lb/>which might 
<lb/>have given offence 
<lb/>to the sensitive<reg>.</reg>
<lb/><persName>M<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">r</hi></hi> MacLehose</persName> of <add place="above"><placeName>Glasgow</placeName></add> tells me he has 
<lb/>ordered 200 copies 
<lb/>so if it does not 
<lb/>sell well a heavy 
<lb/>sin will be at 
<lb/>my door! 

	<pb n="0006" facs="liv_001011_0006"/><!--pb/@n='24v'--> 
<lb/>I only wish it were 
<lb/>in a state for 
<lb/>selling at all<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p><persName>D Livingstone</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I am to get a 
<lb/>view of <placeName>Loando</placeName>
<lb/>from <persName>Captain 
<lb/>Need</persName> - &amp; one of 
<lb/>a Baobab tree<reg>.</reg></p>
			
